Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?

A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,

A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. The charge for insured shipping via Fedex Ground is 30.

title: For Sale:  LNIB Ultra Compact 1911 Springfield Armory 45acp
postcontent: almost new Ultra Compact 1911 45cal, Officers size concealed carry gun. I bought her new and took her to the range to see if she would suffice as a good carry weapon for me. I bought a box of CorBon's, and a box of Hydra-Shocks, I figured if she could eat these without a hickup, then she'll do. The feed ramp and ejection port work had been done at the factory so I was just making sure all worked as claimed. I took the 40 rounds I bought and started filling up the mag's, I mixed fed them into the two mags and proceeded to test her out, no hickups, or stovepipes, and the factory mag locked the slide when empty and dropped out like butter, she function perfectly as claimed, a very nice pistol. I carried her for about a month in a Galco fitted SOB leather holster, then put her in the bottom of my gun safe, where she has sit since the Clinton Administration. She has had a total of 40 rounds down the tube, and is in near perfect condition. The hardcase and all the paperwork, as well as an extra mag, the gun only came with one, is included. Unobstructed panoramic views of the azure sea dotted with sail boats range from Jost Van Dyke and Sandy Cay over to the surf break at Cane Garden Bay. The surf break at Little Apple Bay is just below and is a great view and entertaining in the winter months. 

The location is perfect with easy access to Little Apple Bay and Long Bay beaches. Smuggler's Cove beach is a short drive away. Many restaurants and bars within a short drive include Sugar Mill, Palm's Delight and Long Bay's two restaurants are within a two minute drive; The Bomba Shack, home of the famous Full Moon Party, is a two minute drive, Jolly Roger, Pusser's Landing are within a five minute drive. West End Ferry to Jost Van Dyke, St. Thomas and St. John is a five minute drive. Road Town is a 25 - 30 minute drive, Beef Island airport is a 45 minute drive. 

Little Apple Bay and Long Bay are a 5-10 minute walk down but a bit longer walk up.
